<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-04-01T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-04-01T06:00:00-05:00" n="274" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d274">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Advisory Committee/33:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland (<persName type="from">Wilson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-04-01T12:00:00+01:00">April 1,
                                1933—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received April 1—8:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>160. Your 92, March 31, 6 p.m. I entirely share your views as to the
                            inadvisability of our accepting any responsibility as to a decision
                            which rightly rests with the League of Nations. Nothing was further from
                            my mind than to urge such a course. My telegrams which I have just
                            reviewed were written with the idea of conveying a warning as to how the
                            situation was developing here.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>